quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  3,92,"You will not attain true goodness until you give of what you love. Whatever you give away, Allah knows it"
  3,93,"All food was lawful for the tribe of Israel except what Israel made unlawful for himself before the Torah was sent down. Say, ´Bring the Torah and read it out if you are telling the truth.´"
  3,94,"So any who, after this, invent a lie against Allah are indeed wrongdoers"
  3,95,"Say, ´Allah speaks the truth, so follow the religion of Ibrahim, a man of pure natural belief. He was not one of the idolaters.´"
  3,96,"The first House established for mankind was that at Bakka, a place of blessing and a guidance for all beings"
  3,97,"In it are Clear Signs — the Maqam of Ibrahim. All who enter it are safe. Hajj to the House is a duty owed to Allah by all mankind — those who can find a way to do it. But if anyone is kafir, Allah is Rich Beyond Need of any being"
  3,98,"Say, ´People of the Book, why do you reject Allah´s Signs when Allah is witness of everything you do?´"
  3,99,"Say, ´People of the Book, why do you bar those who have iman from the Way of Allah, desiring to make it crooked, when you yourselves are witnesses to it? Allah is not unaware of what you do.´"
  3,100,"You who have iman! if you obey a group of those given the Book, they will make you revert to being kafir after you have had iman"